{
    "level": "B1",
    "intro": "In this topic, you will learn to form <strong>passive state with modal verbs</strong>: can, must, should, may, might, could. Basic formula: <strong>modal + be + V3</strong>.",
    "rules": [
        {
            "label": "Formula",
            "color": "emerald",
            "text": "<strong>modal + be + V3</strong>:",
            "example": "It must be done today."
        },
        {
            "label": "Possibility",
            "color": "blue",
            "text": "<strong>can/could + be + V3</strong>:",
            "example": "This can be fixed easily."
        },
        {
            "label": "Necessity",
            "color": "rose",
            "text": "<strong>must/should + be + V3</strong>:",
            "example": "The rules must be followed."
        }
    ]
}

{
    "title": "1. The basic structure of the Modal Passive",
    "intro": "The passive voice with modal verbs always uses <strong>modal + be + V3</strong>:",
    "items": [
        {
            "label": "Formula",
            "title": "modal + be + V3",
            "subtitle": "be is always in the infinitive, V3 is the third form of the verb"
        },
        {
            "label": "Without that",
            "title": "Without the particle to",
            "subtitle": "Modal verbs be are followed by without to"
        },
        {
            "label": "Unchanged V3",
            "title": "V3 does not change",
            "subtitle": "Past Participle is always in one form"
        },
        {
            "label": "All subjects",
            "title": "For all subjects",
            "subtitle": "The structure is the same for I/he/they"
        }
    ]
}

{
    "title": "2. Can/Could + be + V3 (possibility, ability)",
    "sections": [
        {
            "label": "can be + V3",
            "color": "emerald",
            "description": "<strong>Possibility</strong> or <strong>ability</strong> to be an action. Present.",
            "examples": [
                {
                    "en": "This problem can be solved easily.",
                    "ua": "This problem can be solved easily."
                },
                {
                    "en": "The document can be downloaded from the website.",
                    "ua": "The document can be downloaded from the website."
                },
                {
                    "en": "English can be learned online.",
                    "ua": "English can be learned online."
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "label": "could be + V3",
            "color": "sky",
            "description": "<strong>Conditional possibility</strong> or possibility in the past.",
            "examples": [
                {
                    "en": "The work could be finished tomorrow.",
                    "ua": "The work could be finished tomorrow."
                },
                {
                    "en": "This issue could be resolved with more time.",
                    "ua": "This issue could be resolved with more time."
                },
                {
                    "en": "The building could be seen from far away.",
                    "ua": "The building could be seen from far away."
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "label": "Denial",
            "color": "rose",
            "description": "<strong>cannot (can't) / could not (couldn't) + be + V3</strong>",
            "examples": [
                {
                    "en": "This error cannot be fixed.",
                    "ua": "This error cannot be fixed."
                },
                {
                    "en": "The package couldn't be delivered.",
                    "ua": "The package couldn't be delivered."
                }
            ]
        }
    ]
}

{
    "title": "3. Must/Have to + be + V3 (necessity)",
    "sections": [
        {
            "label": "must be + V3",
            "color": "rose",
            "description": "<strong>Strong necessity</strong> or obligation. Order, rule.",
            "examples": [
                {
                    "en": "This task must be done today.",
                    "ua": "This task must be done today."
                },
                {
                    "en": "The rules must be followed.",
                    "ua": "The rules must be followed."
                },
                {
                    "en": "All documents must be signed.",
                    "ua": "All documents must be signed."
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "label": "has to / have to be + V3",
            "color": "amber",
            "description": "Necessity due to external circumstances. <strong>have to</strong> has forms in different tenses.",
            "examples": [
                {
                    "en": "The work has to be finished by Friday.",
                    "ua": "The work has to be finished by Friday."
                },
                {
                    "en": "The application had to be submitted yesterday.",
                    "ua": "The application had to be submitted yesterday."
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "label": "Denial",
            "color": "rose",
            "description": "<strong>must not (mustn't)</strong> is a prohibition. <strong>don't have to</strong> — not necessarily.",
            "examples": [
                {
                    "en": "This button must not be pressed.",
                    "ua": "This button must not be pressed."
                },
                {
                    "en": "The report doesn't have to be submitted today.",
                    "ua": "The report doesn't have to be submitted today."
                }
            ]
        }
    ]
}

{
    "title": "4. Should/Ought to + be + V3 (recommendation)",
    "sections": [
        {
            "label": "should be + V3",
            "color": "blue",
            "description": "<strong>Advice</strong> or <strong>recommendation</strong>. What is right or desirable to do.",
            "examples": [
                {
                    "en": "The report should be checked before submission.",
                    "ua": "The report should be checked before submission."
                },
                {
                    "en": "These instructions should be followed carefully.",
                    "ua": "These instructions should be followed carefully."
                },
                {
                    "en": "Mistakes should be corrected immediately.",
                    "ua": "Mistakes should be corrected immediately."
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "label": "ought to be + V3",
            "color": "sky",
            "description": "Same as <strong>should</strong>, but more formal. Rarely used.",
            "examples": [
                {
                    "en": "The project ought to be completed soon.",
                    "ua": "The project ought to be completed soon."
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "label": "Denial",
            "color": "rose",
            "description": "<strong>should not (shouldn't) + be + V3</strong>",
            "examples": [
                {
                    "en": "This information should not be shared.",
                    "ua": "This information should not be shared."
                },
                {
                    "en": "The door shouldn't be left open.",
                    "ua": "The door shouldn't be left open."
                }
            ]
        }
    ]
}

{
    "title": "5. May/Might + be + V3 (probability, permission)",
    "sections": [
        {
            "label": "may be + V3",
            "color": "amber",
            "description": "<strong>Probability</strong> (possible) or <strong>permission</strong> (formal).",
            "examples": [
                {
                    "en": "The package may be delivered today.",
                    "ua": "The package may be delivered today."
                },
                {
                    "en": "This issue may be discussed at the meeting.",
                    "ua": "This issue may be discussed at the meeting."
                },
                {
                    "en": "Photos may be taken during the event.",
                    "ua": "Photos may be taken during the event."
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "label": "might be + V3",
            "color": "sky",
            "description": "Less likely than <strong>may</strong>. \"Possible, but unlikely.\"",
            "examples": [
                {
                    "en": "The project might be postponed.",
                    "ua": "The project might be postponed."
                },
                {
                    "en": "The error might be caused by the update.",
                    "ua": "The error might be caused by the update."
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "label": "Denial",
            "color": "rose",
            "description": "<strong>may not / might not + be + V3</strong>",
            "examples": [
                {
                    "en": "The results may not be ready yet.",
                    "ua": "The results may not be ready yet."
                }
            ]
        }
    ]
}

{
    "title": "6. Questions with modals in the passive",
    "sections": [
        {
            "label": "Yes/No question",
            "color": "blue",
            "description": "<strong>Modal + S + be + V3?</strong>",
            "examples": [
                {
                    "en": "Can this problem be solved?",
                    "ua": "Can this problem be solved?"
                },
                {
                    "en": "Must the task be done today?",
                    "ua": "Must the task be done today?"
                },
                {
                    "en": "Should the report be submitted now?",
                    "ua": "Should the report be submitted now?"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "label": "Wh question",
            "color": "sky",
            "description": "<strong>Wh-word + modal + S + be + V3?</strong>",
            "examples": [
                {
                    "en": "How can this be fixed?",
                    "ua": "How can this be fixed?"
                },
                {
                    "en": "When should the work be finished?",
                    "ua": "When should the work be finished?"
                },
                {
                    "en": "Where must the documents be signed?",
                    "ua": "Where must the documents be signed?"
                }
            ]
        }
    ]
}

{
    "title": "7. Conjugation of modals in the passive",
    "intro": "The main modal verbs with the passive state:",
    "rows": [
        {
            "en": "can be + V3",
            "ua": "can be + V3",
            "note": "This can be done easily."
        },
        {
            "en": "could be + V3",
            "ua": "could be + V3",
            "note": "It could be finished tomorrow."
        },
        {
            "en": "must be + V3",
            "ua": "must be + V3",
            "note": "It must be done now."
        },
        {
            "en": "should be + V3",
            "ua": "should be + V3",
            "note": "It should be checked."
        },
        {
            "en": "may be + V3",
            "ua": "may be + V3",
            "note": "It may be delayed."
        },
        {
            "en": "might be + V3",
            "ua": "might be + V3",
            "note": "It might be cancelled."
        }
    ]
}

{
    "title": "8. Typical mistakes",
    "items": [
        {
            "label": "Error 1",
            "color": "rose",
            "title": "Using to before be.",
            "wrong": "It must to be done.",
            "right": "✅ It must be done."
        },
        {
            "label": "Error 2",
            "color": "amber",
            "title": "Incorrect form of be.",
            "wrong": "It can is done.",
            "right": "✅ It can be done."
        },
        {
            "label": "Error 3",
            "color": "sky",
            "title": "Using V1 instead of V3.",
            "wrong": "It should be do.",
            "right": "✅ It should be done."
        }
    ]
}
